Here’s why everyone needs to #boycott @tremainedance who are ANTISEMITIC
🚫🚫🚫
@palmbeachada performed a beautifully choreographed piece in respect to the Holocaust. That is a historical event that anyone can create art too. This is protected by the first amendment and the EXACT purpose of #art is to stir the audiences emotions in times of difficulties and to remember history. Instead of adjudicating the Holocaust piece as normal procedure, Terry the owner decided to WIPE AWAY THE DANCE as if it never was performed by the hard working dancers. Terry let NONE JEWISH COMPLAINING PARENTS who acted offended dictate the decision of going against protocol and not scoring the piece or even announcing what award was given. Mind you, Palm Beach Academy of Dance Arts has a large amount of Jewish students, all of their families were grateful for this emotional piece bringing remembrance to a horrific time in history that SHOULD NEVER BE FORGOTTEN. Terry’s decision to not properly judge the piece and allow none Jewish snowflake ❄️ parents to erase this performance in Orlando last weekend has now taken action as an ANTISEMITE. In our Jewish culture we are raised to NEVER FORGET HISTORY so we can make sure it never happens again. The north of Israel got barraged  with missiles 2 days ago but you don’t see it in the news. We the Jewish people are asking everyone to speak up, create art and talk about what is currently going on! 
💃🏻 I am posting this piece from @danceonfox that is in remembrance of World War 2 choreographed by @tyce82 This is proof that art is needed and allowed to be created and never should be erased. This case could become legal and I AM ASKING ALL MY SUPPORTERS TO SEND YOUR COMPLAINTS OF ANTISEMITISM TO TREMAINE! If we don’t stand up for freedom of speech, your rights will be erased like Terry did with this studios piece.
